00:07:54,205 --> 00:07:57,641
Don't worry, baby. I got lots of knives.

73
00:07:58,510 --> 00:08:01,570
- What are you going to do for us?
- I was gonna sing.

74
00:08:01,779 --> 00:08:05,146
- You don't have to sing, honey.
- We know our rights.

75
00:08:05,316 --> 00:08:09,514
- You can't refuse her an audition.
- She's not supposed to sing her audition.

76
00:08:09,687 --> 00:08:14,750
Please, excuse me, if you don't mind.
See, honey, you don't have to sing for us...

77
00:08:14,926 --> 00:08:18,692
...because this is the drama department.
- When she sings, it is drama.

78
00:08:18,997 --> 00:08:21,591
- What's your name, honey?
- Finsecker.

79
00:08:24,102 --> 00:08:25,433
Doris Finsecker.

80
00:08:31,409 --> 00:08:34,469
- Hi.
- How do you do?

81
00:08:34,646 --> 00:08:36,739
- What's your name?
- Ralph Garci.

82
00:08:37,115 --> 00:08:41,279
- Who was your teacher?
- Well, my father taught me.

83
00:08:41,452 --> 00:08:46,219
He's doing some work for the government.
I'm actually not supposed to talk about it...

84
00:08:46,424 --> 00:08:52,693
...but my father played some of the
most beautiful symphonies...

85
00:08:52,864 --> 00:08:55,560
...in the whole world once.
- What did he play?

86
00:08:56,768 --> 00:08:58,736
Trombones.

87
00:08:59,737 --> 00:09:02,103
And French horns.

88
00:09:03,708 --> 00:09:04,697
English horns.

89
00:09:06,811 --> 00:09:08,870
- Saxophones.
- Anything else?

90
00:09:09,080 --> 00:09:10,411
Yeah.

91
00:09:11,849 --> 00:09:16,877
- Bongos, maracas, that sort of stuff.
- What did he teach you?

92
00:09:25,129 --> 00:09:26,528
Try the dance department.

93
00:09:31,235 --> 00:09:32,429
Yeah, tell him.

94
00:09:33,237 --> 00:09:35,535
We can't afford a professional
children's school.

95
00:09:38,242 --> 00:09:39,539
Okay, sing and then act.

96
00:09:43,614 --> 00:09:45,343
I'm a little nervous.

97
00:09:45,549 --> 00:09:50,316
Don't be shy, Sheila. Come over here.
What are you going to do?

98
00:09:50,588 --> 00:09:53,580
- I'm doing The Towering Inferno.
- What?

99
00:09:54,858 --> 00:09:58,021
- You know, the movie?
- Oh.

100
00:09:58,462 --> 00:10:01,625
All right, I'm playing O.J. Simpson.
I'm in this building.

101
00:10:01,799 --> 00:10:05,428
There's fire all around, right?
So I go to the elevator.

102
00:10:05,636 --> 00:10:09,629
Think of it as a concentration exercise.
Just sing to Michael...

103
00:10:09,840 --> 00:10:15,301
...and don't worry about anybody else.
- I don't think I can do that. I can't just stare.

104
00:10:15,512 --> 00:10:17,139
He won't mind.

105
00:10:20,584 --> 00:10:24,850
- Waiting for the elevator.
- Press the button, Doris.

106
00:10:29,860 --> 00:10:31,122
Her brother Harvey.

107
00:10:52,750 --> 00:10:55,685
Doesn't come, so now I'm getting mad.

108
00:11:36,060 --> 00:11:40,554
Finally it comes, so I get in.
Okay, and there's people all around.

109
00:11:40,731 --> 00:11:43,256
And they're looking right at me.

110
00:12:29,747 --> 00:12:33,774
Yeah, my father taught me. I'm not
supposed to talk about him right now.

111
00:12:33,951 --> 00:12:36,749
He's doing a little bit of work
for the government, but...

112
00:12:36,920 --> 00:12:41,152
My father is very, very famous.
He danced with the Rockettes.

113
00:12:41,692 --> 00:12:43,751
Sure. Would you begin, please?

114
00:12:45,295 --> 00:12:48,264
- I'll be doing "Swanee River" for you.
- Okay.

115
00:12:48,432 --> 00:12:50,992
And...

116
00:12:51,168 --> 00:12:56,105
Hon? "Swanee River," please.
Hit it.

117
00:13:00,344 --> 00:13:04,110
Doris, what would you do
if you don't make it?

118
00:13:04,681 --> 00:13:05,773
We'll make it.

119
00:13:06,383 --> 00:13:08,510
Next, please.

120
00:13:09,019 --> 00:13:11,954
But I that am not shaped
for sportive tricks...

121
00:13:12,122 --> 00:13:15,023
...nor made to court
an amorous looking glass...

122
00:13:15,192 --> 00:13:18,389
...I that am... Cheated of...
Oh, I'm sorry.

123
00:13:34,845 --> 00:13:37,075
Why don't you try
the drama department.

124
00:13:37,281 --> 00:13:42,548
If again "it was not well cut,"
he'd answer, I spake not true:

125
00:13:42,719 --> 00:13:45,085
This is called the Reply Churlish.

126
00:13:45,422 --> 00:13:48,414
Nobody talks about it,
but there's a quota system.

127
00:13:48,592 --> 00:13:53,495
Your chances are better if you're black,
Puerto Rican or everything, like me.

128
00:13:53,664 --> 00:13:57,964
- I am Puerto Rican.
- Not on your paper you ain't, Ralph Garci.

129
00:13:58,135 --> 00:14:01,901
- Your daddy doing government work.
- That's the truth.

130
00:14:02,206 --> 00:14:06,370
And he left you his tap shoes, right?
Does he work for Pepsi-Cola too?

131
00:14:07,110 --> 00:14:08,168
Be careful.

132
00:14:08,445 --> 00:14:11,073
- To the left. Left.
- Come the other way.

133
00:14:11,281 --> 00:14:12,908
All right.

134
00:14:13,083 --> 00:14:15,711
Easy, now. Straight back, Bruno?

135
00:14:17,554 --> 00:14:20,546
- Where do you want this at?
- Far corner.

136
00:14:23,026 --> 00:14:24,891
How do you do?

137
00:14:25,128 --> 00:14:26,925
Okay. Fine.

138
00:14:27,097 --> 00:14:31,363
Great. Look, I'll do that. You just go
and get the rest of the stuff, okay?

139
00:14:31,535 --> 00:14:33,594
Oh, Martelli. Bruno Martelli.

140
00:14:33,937 --> 00:14:37,304
Would you like to set up
your equipment, Mr. Martelli?

141
00:14:42,646 --> 00:14:44,204
Who taught you?

142
00:14:44,381 --> 00:14:50,115
Who taught me? My father, he taught me.
He's in Spain. He makes Italian Westerns.

143
00:14:50,320 --> 00:14:54,620
- Why do you want to go to school here?
- Because Freddie went here.

144
00:14:54,892 --> 00:14:58,851
- Freddie?
- Freddie Prinze. He's great. He's the best.

145
00:14:59,029 --> 00:15:02,760
- So you want to be an actor, huh?
- Yeah, sure, I want to be an actor.

146
00:15:02,933 --> 00:15:05,458
Judy, Judy, Judy.
Top of the world, Ma.

147
00:15:05,636 --> 00:15:10,335
We don't want you to perform. We want
to see who you are. You understand?

148
00:15:10,641 --> 00:15:12,905
- Right.
- Use your own experience.

149
00:15:13,277 --> 00:15:16,246
Be simple, be honest,
but most of all, be yourself.

150
00:15:16,880 --> 00:15:20,782
- Be honest. Be simple. Be yourself?
- Be yourself.

151
00:15:22,286 --> 00:15:26,655
I'm God, see?
And God is Puerto Rican, you got that? Now.

152
00:15:27,257 --> 00:15:31,421
God works in a casa de steam, you know.
It's a steam bath, right?

153
00:15:31,595 --> 00:15:37,727
And he's talking to this angel. This angel is
a computer. Right? An electronic computer.

154
00:15:37,901 --> 00:15:42,736
I'm God, see? That's why I'm standing
on this chair, you got that? Good.

155
00:15:52,182 --> 00:15:55,674
Does he wanna be a musician
or an airline pilot?

156
00:15:56,787 --> 00:16:00,723
Mr. Martelli. We are ready when you are.
Would you care to begin?

157
00:16:00,924 --> 00:16:03,518
Oh, okay. Sure.

158
00:16:28,552 --> 00:16:29,541
Mr. Martelli.

159
00:16:32,022 --> 00:16:33,990
Mr. Martelli.

160
00:16:38,061 --> 00:16:39,221
Mr. Martelli!

161
00:16:41,264 --> 00:16:44,927
Thank you. One instrument
at a time will be quite sufficient.

162
00:16:45,135 --> 00:16:47,933
I could do it in 4/4
if you prefer a disco beat.

163
00:18:16,660 --> 00:18:19,356
She's a disaster.

164
00:18:22,532 --> 00:18:28,300
Romeo, wherefore art thou Romeo?
Deny thy father and refuse thy name.

165
00:18:28,472 --> 00:18:31,339
Or, if thou wilt not,
be but sworn my love...

166
00:18:31,508 --> 00:18:36,377
...and then I'll no longer be a Capu...
Capu... Capu-something.

167
00:18:36,546 --> 00:18:40,778
- Capulet.
- Capu... Like Cappelletti, the football player?

168
00:18:40,951 --> 00:18:43,112
- Something like that.
- That's what I mean.

169
00:18:47,491 --> 00:18:50,585
- Where's his application?
- He doesn't have one.

170
00:18:50,760 --> 00:18:52,955
Well, get him one.

171
00:19:11,114 --> 00:19:14,083
- What do you call that?
- Wicked.

172
00:19:26,763 --> 00:19:28,196
Thou art thyself.

173
00:19:28,365 --> 00:19:31,596
Thou art not a Montagoo...
Montagazz... Who knows?

174
00:19:31,768 --> 00:19:37,502
Okay. This is the last day of auditions.
We've seen a lot of students. We're punchy.

175
00:19:37,707 --> 00:19:43,202
We're gonna take a break. Go next door
to Mrs. Shime. Have her audition you.

176
00:19:43,380 --> 00:19:46,508
- Right next door.
- I tell her that you sent me?

177
00:19:46,683 --> 00:19:48,583
- Yeah.
- All right.

178
00:19:48,785 --> 00:19:50,184
By the way...

179
00:19:50,353 --> 00:19:54,517
...you were reading the girl's part.
- Shit.

180
00:19:55,659 --> 00:19:59,618
- You're not into high school, remember?
- I'm into dancing.

181
00:19:59,796 --> 00:20:05,132
You're into ass, you mean.
You don't have to go to high school for that.

182
00:20:05,302 --> 00:20:10,296
- I was doing you a favor, remember?
- Some fat fucking favor.

183
00:20:11,508 --> 00:20:17,140
Green. Take your things to the third floor.
Give your forms to the senior on the door.

184
00:20:17,480 --> 00:20:22,144
Okay, you go downstairs,
change in the girls' room and wait for him.

185
00:20:22,319 --> 00:20:25,618
I'm through?
I don't have to dance anymore?

186
00:20:25,822 --> 00:20:28,814
Where you going, Leroy?
He's in and I'm out, right?

187
00:20:29,025 --> 00:20:35,055
Well, fuck you, Leroy! This was my audition,
remember? You're not into high school.

188
00:20:35,232 --> 00:20:40,795
We were rehearsing to get me into this
school, not you, you fucker! It's not fair!

189
00:20:41,004 --> 00:20:44,735
I didn't want to come here anyway.
This school sucks.

190
00:20:44,941 --> 00:20:47,171
You've done me a favor, shithead.

191
00:20:47,377 --> 00:20:51,609
You saved me four fucking years
from this ass-licking school!

192
00:20:51,815 --> 00:20:55,148
You looking at one happy lady!

193
00:20:56,419 --> 00:21:00,185
